    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://newyork.craigslist.org/que/lab/6045631582.html"></div>
        </div>
Department:  Environmental Services<br>
<br>
Reports to: Vice President of Operations and Director of Business Services <br>
<br>
Experience and Qualifications: <br>
•	High School Diploma or equivalent, Bachelor's Degree preferred <br>
	MUST have experience in healthcare with article 28 <br>
•	Minimum of Five (5) to Seven (7) years of maintenance experience in an ambulatory surgical, hospital or similar setting<br>
•	Experience in life-safety systems, work order management and preventive maintenance systems <br>
•	Experience with AAAHC or similar accreditation and compliance requirements <br>
•	Certification in areas including but not limited to Medical Gas Management, Fire and Facility Safety, preferred <br>
<br>
Job Summary:<br>
<br>
The Facility Maintenance Manager has the overall responsibility for operations and maintenance of the facility. The person will coordinate and direct activities to insure continuous efficient, economical and compliant operations of the Center's building, facility systems and related equipment.  The person is responsible for complying with AAAHC standards, the Center's policy and procedures and its Quality Assurance programs and standards. <br>
<br>
Responsibilities:<br>
<br>
1.	To conduct and oversee all preventive and corrective maintenance programs<br>
2.	To evaluate all maintenance work orders, to set priorities and to carry out or assign work orders to staff or outside vendors and suppliers<br>
3.	In conjunction with the Director of Business Services and the Vice President of Operations, to hire contractors or subcontractors regarding security, construction, safety, materials, environmental management project management to perform maintenance work in an efficient and cost effective manner <br>
4.	To work departmental with Directors, Supervisors and Managers to address all Compliance issues, maintaining required logs and documentation <br>
<br>
5.	To monitor all facility operations and systems preparing daily and monthly work schedules <br>
6.	To maintain all maintenance records<br>
7.	To purchase supplies from approved sources and per specifications <br>
8.	To conduct training on life safety &amp; facility systems and programs<br>
9.	To work with Business Services and Operations to maintain all appropriate logs, permits and licensing <br>
10.	To provide reports on all life safety and maintenance issues<br>
11.	To perform routine inspections on HVAC, emergency and disaster systems and equipment<br>
12.	 To apply principles of critical thinking to a variety of practical and emergent situations and to accurately follow standardized procedures that may call for deviations<br>
13.	To be able to apply sound judgement beyond a specific set of instructions and to apply knowledge to different factual situations<br>
14.	To always be alert, paying close attention to detail<br>
15.	To be able to work under stress on a regular or continuous basis<br>
16.	 To perform other duties as assigned<br>
17.	To manage and maintain departmental responsiveness to all facility management and environment of care needs<br>
18.	To retain and advance as needed a specific knowledge of the Clinic's medical gas supply and delivery activities<br>
19.	To create a schedule of routine evaluation to ensure facility compliance with all regulatory requirements<br>
20.	To establish safety protocols for fire, flood and potential hazards<br>
21.	To initiate and address all safety measures throughout the Clinic<br>
22.	To ensure the environment is appropriately maintained at all times<br>
    </section>

